Package com.kicas.rp.data

Class RegionLookupTable

java.lang.Object
com.kicas.rp.data.RegionLookupTable
public class RegionLookupTable extends Object
Allows for regions to be quickly found a various locations through a hash-table-style algorithm.

    • getHighestPriorityRegionAt

      public Region getHighestPriorityRegionAt(org.bukkit.Location loc)
      Returns the region with the highest priority at the given location. If two regions have the same priority, then the region with a parent will be considered as having a higher priority. If there are no regions at the given location, then null is returned.
      Parameters:
      loc - the location.
      Returns:
      the region with the highest priority at the given location, or null if there are no regions at the given location.

    • getLowestPriorityRegionAtIgnoreY

      public Region getLowestPriorityRegionAtIgnoreY(org.bukkit.Location loc)
      Returns the region with the lowest priority at the given location. The returned region is guaranteed to not have a parent.
      Parameters:
      loc - the location.
      Returns:
      the region with the lowest priority at the given location, or null if there are no regions at the given location without a parent.

    • getHighestPriorityRegionAtIgnoreY

      public Region getHighestPriorityRegionAtIgnoreY(org.bukkit.Location loc)
      Returns the region with the highest priority at the given location's x and z values. If two regions have the same priority, then the region with a parent will be considered as having a higher priority.If there are no regions at the given location, then null is returned.
      Parameters:
      loc - the location.
      Returns:
      the region with the highest priority at the given location's x and z values, or null if there are no regions at the given location.
